HEADWORD: Serrulation
<hw>Ser`ru*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of being notched minutely, like a fine saw.</def>
<rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the teeth in a serrulate margin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serry</ent>⟦br⟧
